  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CSR-facility. Forest of the World. Creating shared value in the Honduran Forestry Sector</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The purpose of the project is to engage the national forest authorities, the private timber industry and community forestry groups in Honduras in dialogue with the aim to find solutions to the rapid deforestation and widespread trade in illegal timber, through the promotion of Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR) and inclusive green growth as a potential business case. This includes the use of the international Forestry Stewardship Council (FSC) certification as a framework for sustainable forest management and the establishment of business relations between community forestry groups and the timber transformation industry in Honduras and internationally. The 3-year project was granted in December 2013.</narrative>
  </description>
